## Verdict (short)

**Primary locus: spurious / over-aggressive detection**, not broken slide math. `pathWalkCircle` **truncates only** (no tangential slide). `CollisionResolve` **does** project the remaining `(1 − t)` step via `SingleSlide`, but that only runs after a contact is recorded — and face-B captures are almost all **center `PWR_WalkOk` + circle-only boundary grazes** that should not become blocking `RR_Resolved` events.

The visible 0.10–0.23 m per-frame clip is **`step × (1 − circleHitTime)` short of intended end** (lost forward motion), **not** a reversal past the frame start. It matches **“truncate at contact + no effective slide replay”** when resolution stops at the contact waypoint.

---

## 1. `pathWalkCircleGetIds` → `pathWalkCircle`: truncate, no slide

After a blocking circle contact, `pathWalkCircleGetIds` stores `circleHitTime = hitRange.getMin()` (FWD branch, no `wallEpsilon`):

```2909:2916:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp
				else
				{
					// Non-crossable edge hit - record the hit

					circleHitTime = hitRange.getMin();
					circleHitTriId = currentTriId;
					circleHitEdge = i;
					hitAnything = true;
```

For `PWR_HitEdge`, `pathWalkCircle` calls `makeHitResult2`, which sets position to **linear truncation** along `delta` — no edge-aligned slide vector:

```1688:1714:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp
void FloorMesh::makeHitResult2 ( Vector const & begin, Vector const & delta, int centerTriId, int hitTriId, int hitEdgeId, float hitTime, FloorLocator & result ) const
{
	Segment3d edge = getTriangle(hitTriId).getEdgeSegment(hitEdgeId);

	Vector endPoint = begin + delta * hitTime;

	Vector contactPoint = Distance2d::ClosestPointSeg(endPoint,edge);
	Vector contactNormal = endPoint - contactPoint;

	contactNormal.y = 0.0f;

	IGNORE_RETURN(contactNormal.normalize());

	// ----------

	result = FloorLocator(this,endPoint);
	// ...
	result.setTime(hitTime);
	result.setContactNormal(contactNormal);
```

`pathWalkCircle` dispatch for circle hits:

```2556:2562:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp
	else if((walkResult == PWR_HitEdge) || (walkResult == PWR_InContact))
	{
		makeHitResult2( begin, delta, centerTriId, hitId, hitEdgeId, hitTime, result );

		result.setRadius(radius);

		return walkResult;
```

**Post-contact delta returned to callers:** `delta × hitTime` implicitly (position = `begin + delta × hitTime`). Normal is radial (center → edge), not edge tangent.

---

## 2. `CollisionResolve` replay: slide exists, but only after contact

### Waypoint construction (`CollisionResolve.cpp:364+`)

On first resolvable contact:

```421:463:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp
		Vector contactPoint = moveSeg.atParam(contactCell,contact.m_time);

		outList.push_back( CellPosition(contactCell,contactPoint) );

		MoveSegment secondSeg;

		secondSeg.m_cellA = contactCell;
		secondSeg.m_pointA = contactPoint;

		secondSeg.m_cellB = moveSeg.m_cellB;
		secondSeg.m_pointB = moveSeg.m_pointB;

		if(contact.m_time != 0.0f)
		{
			translateEverything(cellA,extentA,floorContactsA,moveSeg,contact.m_time,ms_ignoreTriId,ms_ignoreEdge);
		}

		// ----------

		int contactCount = ms_contactList.size() + 1;

		if(contactCount == 1)
		{
			Vector delta = secondSeg.getDelta(contactCell);

			Vector slidDelta = Collision3d::SingleSlide(delta,contact.m_normal);

			// Stop resolution if the velocity starts to move backwards

			Vector localStartDelta = CollisionUtils::rotateToCell(startCell,startDelta,contactCell);

			if(slidDelta.dot(localStartDelta) <= 0.0f)
			{
				return RR_Resolved;
			}

			ms_contactList.push_back(contact);

			moveSeg.m_cellA = contactCell;
			moveSeg.m_pointA = contactPoint;

			moveSeg.m_cellB = contactCell;
			moveSeg.m_pointB = contactPoint + slidDelta;
```

- **Contact waypoint:** `begin + delta × circleHitTime` (`atParam`, `CollisionResolve.cpp:65-70`).
- **Remaining motion:** `secondSeg.getDelta()` = `delta × (1 − circleHitTime)`.
- **Slide:** `SingleSlide(remaining, normal)` projects off the inward normal component (`CollisionUtils.cpp:249-315`).
- **Next iteration** (no further hit): pushes final `moveSeg.m_pointB` (`:391`).

### Rewind + replay

```320:339:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp
		Vector resetPos = moveSeg.getBegin(moveSeg.m_cellB);
		// ...
		objectA->setPosition_p(resetPos);

		moveObjectAlong(objectA,positions);
```

`moveObjectAlong` is a straight teleport chain:

```214:228:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp
void moveObjectAlong ( Object * object, CellPositionList const & positions )
{
	int count = positions.size();

	for(int i = 0; i < count; i++)
	{
		// ...
		object->setPosition_p( localEnd );
	}
}
```

### Same-cell horizontal contact — two outcomes

| Path | `positions` | Net vs intended end `begin + delta` |
|------|-------------|----------------------------------------|
| **Slide succeeds** (`slidDelta·startDelta > 0`, 2nd iter clean) | `[contact, contact + SingleSlide(δ(1−t), n)]` | ≈ full step along wall (for a legitimate block) |
| **Slide aborted** (`slidDelta·startDelta ≤ 0`, `:452-454`) | `[contact]` only | **`δ × (1 − t)` short** — stuck at contact |

Floor contact enters resolution via `findContactWithFloor` → `canMove` → `pathWalkCircle`, using `result.getTime()` as `contact.m_time` (`:788-805`).

### Center-cleared asymmetry (face-B smoking gun)

When `centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk`, the filter that would clip circle hits past center exit time **does not run**:

```2838:2841:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp
			if( (centerWalkResult == PWR_ExitedMesh) || (centerWalkResult == PWR_HitPortalEdge) || (centerWalkResult == PWR_HitEdge) )
			{
				if(hitRange.getMin() > centerHitTime) continue;
			}
```

161/162 avatar captures have center `PWR_WalkOk` but still return `PWR_HitEdge`/`PWR_InContact` from the **offset circle**. Resolution has **no** “center cleared → don’t block” branch; any non-`WalkOk` from `canMove` becomes a floor contact (`CollisionResolve.cpp:788-790`).

**For face-B: the stutter is “spurious detection → resolution pipeline runs → often ends at truncate (missing slide),” not “bad `SingleSlide` geometry” on legitimate center blocks.**

---

## 3. Reconciling 0.10–0.23 m backward clip with code

LOCKED evidence: net forward across frames, per-frame backward clip vs intended end.

**Not reversal past frame start (normal case).** Same-cell `resetPos = begin` (last frame). FWD contacts have `circleHitTime ≥ 0`, so `contactPoint = begin + δ×t` is **forward of** `begin`. Replay never ends behind `begin` unless the rare PEN branch fires with negative `t` and `|step×t| ≤ wallEpsilon` (`:2880-2903`, `:69`).

**Backward clip magnitude = lost forward motion:**

\[
|\text{intended} - \text{resolved}| \approx \|\delta\| \times (1 - \text{circleHitTime})
\]

when resolution stops at contact (`:452-454`, one waypoint).

Examples from LOCKED data:
- `step ≈ 0.08–0.44`, `circleHitTime` spans `<0.01` to `>0.4`
- `step=0.20`, `t=0.45` → loss `0.11 m` ✓
- `step=0.30`, `t=0.30` → loss `0.21 m` ✓

The CORNERSNAP rewind log (`posBefore → resetPos`) is the **full-step rewind-then-replay** pattern (`:337-339`), not the net visible clip. Visible jitter is **resolved ≪ intended**, not **resolved < last frame**.

---

## 4. Numerical / step-size tipping points (detection)

`IntersectCircleSeg` itself has **no wall thickness epsilon** — pure FP range math:

```330:350:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/Intersect2d.cpp
Range IntersectCircleSeg ( Circle const & A, Vector const & V, Segment3d const & S )
{
	// ...
	Range slabRange = Intersect1d::IntersectFloatRange( c, v, Range(0.0f,1.0f) );
	Range tubeRange = IntersectCircleLine(A,V,L);
	Range innerRange = Intersect1d::IntersectRanges(tubeRange,slabRange);
	Range beginRange = Intersect2d::IntersectCirclePoint(A,V,S.getBegin());
	Range endRange = Intersect2d::IntersectCirclePoint(A,V,S.getEnd());
	Range outerRange = Containment1d::EncloseRanges(beginRange,innerRange,endRange);
	return outerRange;
}
```

**Step-sensitive comparisons in `pathWalkCircleGetIds` (not in `IntersectCircleSeg` itself):**

| Site | Comparison | Step / FP sensitivity |
|------|------------|----------------------|
| `:2874-2878` | `hitRange.getMin() == hitRange.getMax()` | **Exact FP equality** — grazing contact appears/disappears with rounding/toolchain |
| `:2869-2871` | `contactNormal.dot(V) >= 0.0f` | Grazing angle — tiny FP flip records/loses contact |
| `:2886` | PEN: `contactDistance < wallEpsilon` where `contactDistance = step × \|min\|` | **Scales with step** — larger step accepts more past contacts |
| `:2909-2916` | FWD: **no epsilon gate** | Any forward graze while center walks OK → hard block |
| `:2956-2965` | `contactDist = step × \|circleHitTime\| ≤ wallEpsilon` → `PWR_InContact` | Larger step → more `HitEdge` vs `InContact` at same `t` |
| `:2836` | `hitRange.getMin() > circleHitTime` early-out | Competing hits — order depends on FP min ordering |

`canExitEdge` for `FET_Uncrossable` is a hard `false` (`:1923-1925`) — mesh-boundary edges always block once detected. `intersectEdge` uses the same `IntersectCircleSeg` with `[0,1]` time clip (`:3513-3519`).

**FPS correlation (LOCKED fact 7):** larger per-frame `step` → more/larger-magnitude `PWR_HitEdge` events → larger `(1−t)×step` loss when slide aborts. Retail on identical assets likely **never enters resolution** for these center-OK circle grazes (returns `PWR_WalkOk`), not because `SingleSlide` differs.

---

## Classification

| Hypothesis | Fit |
|------------|-----|
| **Spurious detection** | **Best fit** — center OK + circle graze on `FET_Uncrossable` boundary (`portalId=-1`), FWD branch unguarded, center filter skipped when `PWR_WalkOk` |
| **Missing slide** | **Secondary amplifier** — `:452-454` leaves avatar at truncate; one-waypoint replay |
| **Bad slide** | **Unlikely for parallel wall walk** — `SingleSlide` is standard; would need wrong normal or dot-test false negative |

---

## Recommended fix locus

**Narrowest safe change: detection in `FloorMesh::pathWalkCircleGetIds`**, not `CollisionResolve` replay.

**Primary site:** `FloorMesh.cpp:2909-2930` (FWD forward-graze record branch) — gate symmetrically to PEN (`:2886`) and/or **suppress circle-only blocks when `centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk`** and graze depth ≤ `wallEpsilon` (or equivalent “center cleared” rule at `:2937-3019`).

**Do not** relax `CollisionResolve.cpp:452-454` globally — that widens blast radius for real center blocks.

**Secondary hardening:** `:2874` degenerate graze — replace `min == max` with epsilon band.

---

## Probes if still undecidable at runtime

Add to existing CORNERSNAP probes:

**In `CollisionResolve.cpp` after `:446`:**
```cpp
// LOG: circleHitTime=contact.m_time, step=|delta|, lost=(1-t)*step,
// slidDelta=..., dot=slidDelta.dot(localStartDelta),
// waypoints=positions.size()+1, branch=(dot<=0?"NO_SLIDE":"SLIDE")
```

**In `pathWalkCircleGetIds` at `:2937` when `hitAnything`:**
```cpp
// LOG: centerWalkResult, circleHitTime, contactDist=step*|t|,
// branch FWD/PEN, wouldSuppress=(centerWalk==WalkOk && contactDist<=wallEpsilon)
```

**Decisive split:**
- **`NO_SLIDE` + legitimate contact** → resolution dot-test (`:452`)
- **`SLIDE` + large `(1−t)×step` loss** → bad normal (log `result.getContactNormal()` from `makeHitResult2`)
- **High `wouldSuppress` rate on stutter frames** → detection fix at `:2909` / center-OK gate confirmed
